                    netropy - a XENOmat 2009 retrofixture




netropy - a XENOmat 2009 retrofixture


								strχtrs





		                netropy is a novel kind of lightweight virtual machine for processing structured information. Unlike other VMs such as Java's JVM or the .NET CLR, which in their philosophical foundation are based on ancient Greek ideas about describing the world in terms of abstractions, this inventive technology has no need for defining a new language for its purposes. Instead, it uses a radically different and much simpler approach to information processing, resulting in unparalleled performance and scalability.




                        The core engine is programmed in modestly modern C++*, and (when augmented with streaming compiler technology and a network layer based on the asio C++ library) gives you a full stack platform called the XENOmat.



                        In terms of speed, low overhead and robustness it is well suited for embedded applications and critical infrastructure.
                        Guess which of the processes below is running this server? 


top - 08:44:09 up 39 days,  4:57, 11 users,  load average: 0.20, 0.34, 0.56
Tasks:  4 total,  1 running,  3 sleeping,   0 stopped,   0 zombie
%Cpu(s):  0.7 us,  0.9 sy,  0.3 ni, 98.1 id,  0.0 wa,  0.0 hi,  0.0 si,  0.0 st
KiB Mem:   4048128 total,  3680340 used,   367788 free,   612588 buffers
KiB Swap:  8385532 total,   585036 used,  7800496 free,   912056 cached


